article.headline: St. Francis (NY) thrashes St. Francis (PA) 73-44
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Ben Mockford scored 16 points and St. Francis (NY) broke out to a big first half lead, beating St. Francis (PA) 73-44 on Thursday. The Terriers of St. Francis (NY) outscored the Red Flash of St. Francis (PA) by 23 points in the first half to lead 42-19 lead at the break. The Red Flash managed only a single field goal over a 10 minute stretch in the first period as the Terriers pulled away and went to the bench early giving the starters a rest. The Terriers (16-12, 7-6 Northeast) bench scored 40 points and their tenacious defense shut down Red Flash (8-18, 6-7) scoring opportunities, holding them to just 33 percent shooting. The Terriers dominated the boards 38-24 and shot 54 percent from the field. Earl Brown led Red Flash in scoring with 12 points. The Terriers swept both games against the Red Flash this season.
